%N A395567 Primes of the form (x^2 + y^2 + z^2) / (x*y + x*z + y*z) with integer x, y, z.
%C A395567 It appears that primes of the form 6*k - 1 are terms about 5 times more often than primes 6*k + 1 are (checked up to 10^7).
%e A395567 a(4) = 29 is term since 29 = (1109^2 + 11^2 + 27^2) / (1109*11 + 1109*27 + 11*27).
%e A395567 a(6) = 101 with (x,y,z) = (11321,11,101).
%e A395567 a(7) = 109 with (x,y,z) = (-23,31,103).
